## Fix stale session state leaking between domain switches

Context: When switching domains (e.g. from the Knowledge Graph page), groups,
design layout, mappings, triplestore config, and other characteristics from the
previously loaded domain could persist into the newly loaded domain. The root
cause was that `import_from_file` only replaced session sections that existed
in the incoming data — missing sections were left untouched.

Changes:
1. src/back/objects/session/DomainSession.py — Added `import copy` at module
   level and a full content-section reset at the top of `import_from_file()`.
   Before overlaying new data, ontology, assignment, design_layout,
   domain info, metadata, and triplestore are reset to empty defaults.
   Removed the now-redundant triplestore cleanup at the bottom of the method.

Modified files:
- src/back/objects/session/DomainSession.py

Test result: 1531 passed

