## Show loading spinner when clicking Cross-Domain Bridge links

Context: The previous spinner work covered the graph switcher modal and the
client-side `_switchDomainForBridge` URL-parameter flow, but cross-domain
Bridge links in the entity details panel go through `/resolve?uri=...&domain=...`.
That route performs a server-side domain switch (slow) and then returns a 302
redirect — during this wait the browser shows a blank loading state and no
JavaScript can run, so the "Loading {domain}..." overlay never appeared.

Fix: render an inline `onclick` handler on each bridge anchor that invokes
`showDomainLoading('Loading {target_domain}...')` synchronously before the
navigation starts. The overlay remains visible while the browser waits for the
`/resolve` response and the subsequent redirect to the Knowledge Graph page.

Changes:
1. src/front/static/query/js/query-entity-details.js — Bridges rendered in
   the entity details panel now include an `onclick` attribute that calls
   `showDomainLoading` with the target domain name.
2. src/front/static/query/js/query-sigmagraph.js — Same `onclick`-triggered
   overlay on bridges rendered inside the SigmaGraph entity details section.
3. src/front/static/query/js/query-sigmagraph.js — Right-click node context
   menu "Bridges" path: the delegated click handler that did
   `window.location.href = url` now extracts the target domain from the
   resolve URL and calls `showDomainLoading('Loading {domain}...')` before
   navigating. This was the third bridge entry-point and the reason the
   overlay was still missing for users using the right-click menu.

Modified files:
- src/front/static/query/js/query-entity-details.js
- src/front/static/query/js/query-sigmagraph.js

Test result: 1531 passed

