## Help Center: lock modal height (no resize when switching menu items)

Context: The Help Center modal resized vertically depending on the
active section's content, because Bootstrap's `modal-dialog-scrollable`
only caps the max-height. Switching from a short section (e.g. Welcome)
to a tall one (e.g. FAQ) made the whole window jump. The user asked for
a fixed window height.

Changes:
1. src/front/static/global/css/help-modal.css
   - `.help-modal .modal-content`: forced `height: 88vh` (in addition to
     `max-height: 88vh`) so the dialog keeps a constant size.
   - `.help-modal .modal-body`: pinned with `flex: 1 1 auto; min-height: 0;
     padding: 0; overflow: hidden;` to pass the height down to the
     scrollable inner pane.
   - `.help-modal-body`: `height: 100%; min-height: 0; overflow: hidden;`
     (replaces the former min-/max-height pair).
   - `.help-sidebar` and `.help-content`: added `min-height: 0;` so
     their own `overflow-y: auto;` works inside the flex container.

Net effect: the modal is always 88vh tall; the left rail and the content
panel scroll independently; switching sections never changes the outer
window size.

