## Help Center: fix double vertical scrollbar in tall sections (Starter Guide)

Context: In tall sections such as Starter Guide, the Help Center showed
two vertical scrollbars side-by-side: one from Bootstrap's
`modal-dialog-scrollable` (which enables `overflow-y: auto` on
`.modal-body`) and one from our `.help-content` inner pane. We manage
scrolling ourselves on `.help-content`, so Bootstrap's scroll on the
body was redundant and visually wrong.

Changes:
1. src/front/templates/partials/layout/help_modal.html
   - Removed the `modal-dialog-scrollable` class from the dialog.
     Scrolling is now handled exclusively by `.help-content`.
2. src/front/static/global/css/help-modal.css
   - Reinforced `.help-modal .modal-body` with
     `overflow: hidden !important` and added an explicit
     `.help-modal .modal-body, .help-modal .help-modal-body
     { overflow-x: hidden !important; overflow-y: hidden !important; }`
     rule so no ancestor of `.help-content` ever renders a scrollbar.

Result: a single vertical scrollbar on the content pane only, in every
section (Welcome, Starter Guide, Workflow, FAQ, etc.).

Modified files:
- src/front/templates/partials/layout/help_modal.html
- src/front/static/global/css/help-modal.css

